1 e. "Publish" means to communicate or make information available to another
2 person on a publicly available internet website.
3 f. "Reasonable age verification methods" includes verifying the individual seeking to
4 access the material is eighteen years of age or older by using:
5 (1) A digitized identification card; or
6 (2) Requiring the individual attempting to access the material to comply with a
7 commercial age verification system including the use of:
8 (a) Government-issued identification; or
9 (b) Any commercially reasonable method that relies on public or private
10 transactional data to verify the age of the individual attempting to
11 access the information is eighteen years of age or older.
12 g. "Sexual material harmful to a minor" includes material that:
13 (1) The average individual applying contemporary community standards would
14 find, taking the material as a whole and with respect to a minor, is designed
15 to appeal to or pander to the prurient interest;
16 (2) In a manner patently offensive with respect to a minor, exploits, is devoted
17 to, or principally consists of descriptions of actual, simulated, or animated
18 displays or depictions of:
19 (a) An individual's pubic hair, anus, genitals, or the nipple of the female
20 breast;
21 (b) Touching, caressing, or fondling of nipples, breasts, buttocks, anuses,
22 or genitals; or
23 (c) Sexual intercourse, masturbation, sodomy, bestiality, oral copulation,
24 flagellation, excretory functions, exhibitions, or any other sexual act;
25 and
26 (3) Taken as a whole, lacks serious literary, artistic, political, or scientific value
27 for a minor.
28 h. "Substantial portion" means more than thirty-three and one-third percent of tota l
29 material on a website is sexual material harmful to a minor.
30 i. "Transactional data" means a sequence of information that documents an
31 exchange, agreement, or transfer between an individual, commercial entity, or
